### Explanation of the Algorithm

The algorithm used in the `FindTriangle` class is based on the concept of checking the position of a point relative to the sides of the triangle. It uses the cross-product method to determine if the point is on the same side of each triangle edge as the opposite vertex. If the point is on the same side for all three edges, it is inside the triangle. Additionally, it checks if the point is within a bounding box around the triangle and uses a distance check to account for points near the edges within a small epsilon value. This approach is efficient and handles edge cases like points on the edges or vertices of the triangle.

